<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>TeodorL</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Lurker<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jun 2004<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>veeshanMurtak</b><br /><i><br />
* Poison nukes<br />
Increase Spear of Torment to do 900 damage. Up the mana cost to 370.<br />
<br />
* Ice nukes<br />
Increase Velium Strike to do 1300 damage. Up the mana cost to 430.<br />
</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>I'd have to agree with the changes proposed to the nukes.  At first look, they seemed outrageously high, but I've been looking at the idea of our place within the nuking hierarchy.  Wizards and Mages clearly should be on top.  How the rest filter out I'm not sure.  I personally have no problem with Druids and Enchanters being able to nuke better than I can.  Necros and Clerics?  I don't like that some much.  Hybrids?  We'd better be able to nuke better than them.  <br />
<br />
A quick summary of nukes:<br />
<br />
<table><tr><td ><STRONG>Class</STRONG></td><td ><STRONG>Spell</STRONG></td><td ><STRONG>Cast Time</STRONG></td><td ><STRONG>Recast Time</STRONG></td><td><STRONG>Damage</STRONG></td><td><STRONG>Mana</STRONG></td></tr><tr><td>Beastlord</td><td>Trushar's Frost</td><td align="right">3.2</td><td align="right">30</td><td align="right">742</td><td align="right">274</td></tr><tr><td>Beastlord</td><td>Frost Spear</td><td align="right">3.2</td><td align="right">30</td><td align="right">675</td><td align="right">250</td></tr><tr><td>Cleric</td><td>Order</td><td align="right">6.5</td><td align="right">7</td><td align="right">1210</td><td align="right">401</td></tr><tr><td>Cleric</td><td>Condemnation</td><td align="right">6.5</td><td align="right">7</td><td align="right">1100</td><td align="right">365</td></tr><tr><td>Druid</td><td>Sylvan Fire</td><td align="right">6.25</td><td align="right">2</td><td align="right">1705</td><td align="right">430</td></tr><tr><td>Druid</td><td>Winter's Frost</td><td align="right">6.35</td><td align="right">2</td><td align="right">1550</td><td align="right">390</td></tr><tr><td>Druid</td><td>Summer's Flame</td><td align="right">6.25</td><td align="right">2</td><td align="right">1400</td><td align="right">355</td></tr><tr><td>Enchanter</td><td>Madness of Ikkibi</td><td align="right">6</td><td align="right">8</td><td align="right">1210</td><td align="right">330</td></tr><tr><td>Enchanter</td><td>Insanity</td><td align="right">6</td><td align="right">8</td><td align="right">1100</td><td align="right">300</td></tr><tr><td>Mage</td><td>Firebolt of Tallon</td><td align="right">7</td><td align="right">2</td><td align="right">2000</td><td align="right">500</td></tr><tr><td>Mage</td><td>Rock of Taelosia</td><td align="right">6.35</td><td align="right">2</td><td align="right">1705</td><td align="right">430</td></tr><tr><td>Mage</td><td>Sun Vortex</td><td align="right">6.35</td><td align="right">2</td><td align="right">1550</td><td align="right">390</td></tr><tr><td>Necromancer</td><td>Neurotoxin</td><td align="right">6</td><td align="right">4</td><td align="right">1300</td><td align="right">465</td></tr><tr><td>Ranger</td><td>Sylvan Burn</td><td align="right">3.5</td><td align="right">30</td><td align="right">770</td><td align="right">330</td></tr><tr><td>Ranger</td><td>Frozen Wind</td><td align="right">3.5</td><td align="right">30</td><td align="right">700</td><td align="right">300</td></tr><tr><td>Ranger</td><td>Brushfire</td><td align="right">3.5</td><td align="right">30</td><td align="right">612</td><td align="right">220</td></tr><tr><td>Shadowknight</td><td>Miasmic Wind</td><td align="right">0.5</td><td align="right">45</td><td align="right">660</td><td align="right">247</td></tr><tr><td>Shadowknight</td><td>Spear of Decay</td><td align="right">0.5</td><td align="right">45</td><td align="right">600</td><td align="right">225</td></tr><tr><td>Shaman</td><td>Spear of Torment</td><td align="right">4.2</td><td align="right">2</td><td align="right">675</td><td align="right">275</td></tr><tr><td>Shaman</td><td>Velium Strike</td><td align="right">7.8</td><td align="right">2</td><td align="right">925</td><td align="right">300</td></tr><tr><td>Wizard</td><td>White Fire</td><td align="right">8</td><td align="right">2</td><td align="right">3015</td><td align="right">704</td></tr><tr><td>Wizard</td><td>Strike of Solusek</td><td align="right">8</td><td align="right">2</td><td align="right">2740</td><td align="right">640</td></tr><tr><td>Wizard</td><td>Black Ice</td><td align="right">3</td><td align="right">2</td><td align="right">1045</td><td align="right">280</td></tr></table><br />
<br />
In terms of efficiency (straight damage per mana) we rank as follows:<br />
<br />
Wizards are the tops with 4.28 dmg/mana (SoS and White Fire)<br />
Mages next with 4 dmg/mana (Firebolt of Tallon)<br />
Druids next with 3.97 dmg/mana. (winter's Frost)<br />
Enchanters with 3.66 dmg/mana (Madness of Ikkibi)<br />
Shaman with 3.08 dmg/mana (Velium Strike)<br />
Clerics with 3.02 dmg/mana (Order)<br />
Necromancers with 2.79 dmg/mana (Neurotoxin)<br />
Rangers with 2.78 dmg/mana (Brushfire)<br />
Beastlords with 2.7 dmg/mana (Trushar's Frost)<br />
Shadowknights with 2.67 dmg/mana (Miasmic Wind)<br />
<br />
I was a little surprised here, I expected Sony to give us much less efficient nukes to "balance" against cannibalize.<br />
<br />
Your changes to the nukes would result in a slight decrease in the efficiency of our nukes leaving us exactly where we are.  This is fine.  However it neglects to take in account the changes in dps this would results in.<br />
<br />
A simplistic look at dps would be to evaluate the potential dps from chain casting the nuke (casting nothing but the nuke in question). To calculate this, we need to take the refresh time into account.  The results are as follows:<br />
<br />
Wizards are tops with 301.5 dmg/sec (White Fire)<br />
Mages with 222.2 dmg/sec (Firebolt of Tallon)<br />
Druids with 206.7 dmg/sec (Sylvan Fire)<br />
Necromancers with 130 dmg/sec (Neurotoxin)<br />
Shaman with 108 dmg/sec (Spear of Torment)<br />
Clerics with 89 dmg/sec (Order)<br />
Enchanters with 86 dmg/sec (Madness of Ikkibi)<br />
Hybrids are all less than 25 dmg/sec due to the long recast times on their nukes 30+ sec.<br />
<br />
This analysis is not accurate, fights do not last long enough for nukers to fire off unlimited nukes (disregarding mana constraints)  Instead I like to look at an 18 second window for nuking.  Still sticking to one spell, we get the following dps numbers:<br />
<br />
Wizards with 335 dmg/sec (White Fire)<br />
Mage with 222 dmg/sec (Firebolt of Tallon)<br />
Druid with 189 dmg/sec (Sylvan Fire)<br />
Necromancer with 144 dmg/sec (Neurotoxin)<br />
Shaman with 75 dmg/sec (Spear of Torment)<br />
Cleric with 67.2 dmg/sec (Order)<br />
Enchanter with 67.2 dmg/sec (Madness of Ikkibi)<br />
Ranger with 42.7 dmg/sec (Sylvan Burn)<br />
Beastlord with 41.2 dmg/sec (Trushar's Frost)<br />
Shadowknights with 36.6 dmg/sec (Miasmic Wind)<br />
<br />
I'm still not satisfied with this as an adequate picture of true nuking ability.  Let's assume instead that each nuking class is willing to devote two spell gems to their nukes and is willing to cycle through them to achieve maximum output of damage over the same 18 sec interval.  The numbers:<br />
<br />
Wizards with 335 dmg/sec (White Fire)<br />
Mage with 222 dmg/sec (Firebolt of Tallon)<br />
Druid with 189 dmg/sec (Sylvan Fire)<br />
Necromancer with 144 dmg/sec (Neurotoxin)<br />
Cleric with 128 dmg/sec (Order and Condemnation)<br />
Enchanter with 128 dmg/sec (Madness of Ikkibi and Insanity)<br />
Shaman with 88 dmg/sec (Spear of Torment and Velium strike)<br />
Ranger with 81 dmg/sec (Sylvan Burn and Frozen Wind)<br />
Beastlord with 78 dmg/sec (Trushar's Frost and Frost Spear)<br />
Shadowknights with 70 dmg/sec (Miasmic Wind and Spear of Decay)<br />
<br />
Now the number start to reveal a problem.  Shaman are dipping dangerous low into the realm of hybrid nuking, still better but barely.  Ideally I'd like to see our nuking on par with Clerics and Enchanters, but I'd accept being somewhat below them.  The changes proposed put us at:<br />
<br />
122 dmg/sec (Spear of Torment and Velium strike)<br />
<br />
We're still a step behind Enchanters, Clerics and Necros, but enough ahead of Hybrids to be considered viable sources of dps. (All this hinges off the assumption that while DPS from DoTs can be good, they just don't cut the mustard on the shorter fights)</p>
	
	
	
	
	
