<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Sudedor</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Oracle<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2004<br />
	Location: North Carolina, USA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I really think that increasing mana cost on our nukes is a mistake.  By doing that you are increasing only our "burst" DPS ability.  You aren't really giving us the ability to contribute consistent DPS to a group.  That to me is key.<br />
<br />
It's not how much damage you might be able to do on this one mob, it's how much damage you can do to each and every mob we face.<br />
<br />
What might be interesting to find out, though I have *no* idea how, is how much damage a wizard does to each mob, on average.<br />
<br />
Sure, we can look at their spells, add the cast and recast times and see what their potential DPS is . . . but how much are they actually doing in "live" situations.  I'm fairly certain they aren't sitting back chain casting their top nukes.<br />
<br />
Food for thought.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
