<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>TeodorL</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Lurker<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jun 2004<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I wasn't really comparing potential shaman nukes directly to wizard nukes, but rather trying to create a picture of nuking as a whole.  Looking at the balance of nuking as a whole, we can see how we fare in the "balance".  I don't think shaman nukes should be anywhere near the level of wizard, magician or even druid nukes.  However I would like to see some of the power wielded by clerics *boggle* shared by shaman.<br />
<br />
As far as being able to get one nuke off before the mob is dead, we still have Spear of Torment =/<br />
<br />
Kidding aside, the time on our nukes is indicative of the role we shaman are expected to play.  With their short recast time, the longer the fight the more effective our nukes become.  Clerics and Enchanters are saddled with long recast times on their nukes.  But with shorter fights and pulls sometimes taking longer thant fights, being able to fire off your best nuke in 6 seconds rather than 7.8 can make a world of difference in your ability to contribute.  The 8 second recast time on their nukes (as opposed to our 2) seems like not such a horrible drawback when you only have time to drop one nuke on the mob anyways.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
