	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Gloriana</b><br /><i>Food for what thought? What does comparing potential shaman nukes to wizard nukes have to do with anything? I don't think any of us are asking to do anything close to the nuke damage of a wizard. Personally, I'd like to be able to get ONE nuke off before the damn mob is dead.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>What I was saying is this:<br />
<br />
We all know that Wizards have, by far, the greatest nuking ability in the game.  I agree with this and in no way have I ever said that this should change.  I never intended to even insinuate that we should be close to their ability.<br />
<br />
What I was pondering is more a question of what a Wizard really does.  I know he doesn't start chain casting nukes on incoming.  How many spells does a Wizard cast on a per mob basis?  How much damage does he actually do on a per mob basis?  What percentage of the mobs health is actually taken away by a Wizard?  These are the things I was pondering.<br />
<br />
<br />
Edit:<br />
<br />
Pondering this whole DPS issue further got me to thinking.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>TeodorL</b><br /><i>122 dmg/sec (Spear of Torment and Velium strike)<br />
<br />
We're still a step behind Enchanters, Clerics and Necros, but enough ahead of Hybrids to be considered viable sources of dps. (All this hinges off the assumption that while DPS from DoTs can be good, they just don't cut the mustard on the shorter fights)</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>If we feel that 122 DPS is an acceptable level of DPS for the Shaman, then perhaps we are a lot closer than we think to where we wish to be.<br />
<br />
Tears of Saryn + Velium Strike:<br />
<br />
Assume one wave of Tears is resisted.  (Yea, that does suck, but its reality).  Anyway . . . 2 waves of Tears + Velium Strike = 123.6 DPS.  Add in dogdog's 25 DPS and we're just below and unhasted Ranger, generally thought to be around 157 DPS.<br />
<br />
More food for thought.</p>
	
	
	
	
