	<p>Very nice post, perhaps the best summary of Shaman issues I have seen.<br />
<br />
I would like to throw out a few (tweeks) if you will that you might consider adding.<br />
<br />
1) Pet innate duel wield.  Although I agree 100% with having puppy duel wield, I think that giving Shaman perhaps a couple of levels of weapon summoning spells (with procs) may be a nicer fix (in that "perfect world").<br />
<br />
2) Nukes: I think that a slight reduction in casting times on our DD's is warranted - perhaps 25%.  I'm with Gloriana on this one, not even being able to contribute ANY damage because of our slow casting nukes is enemy #1 - especially on clearing mobs in raids when you do not have slowing duty.<br />
<br />
3) I think that asking for our ancient canny spell to be "store bought" may be a bit ambitious unless it is 50k+ which would require a time sink to make the plat.  Otherwise perhaps make it obtainable for all Shaman with some sort of Quest.<br />
<br />
Purdypog<br />
<br />
PS: It's about the burst damage! Fast fights are the new EQ and that is to be the continued according to the developers.  I couldn't disagree more with Sudedor on that point or on the "phantom 120dps" which really is about 50% of that because most of us still have to malos, slow, buff, heal and canny here and there.</p>
	
	
	
	
