	<p>For gods sake Purdy read in context.<br />
<br />
That figure is based on the assumption that Slowing is irrelevant in the encounter.  There are many mobs that die in under 30 seconds in current content.  For those mobs, Slow is not relevant as it is mitigated and only affects 30% of the fight.  This is about being able to make a difference in that fight, where we are NOT slowing.<br />
<br />
If you aren't to that content yet, great.  Enjoy your Shaman.  If you are, I cannot understand why increasing your sustained potential DPS isn't an option you care for.  I for one would like to be relevant to a group in all content, outside of my increasingly devalued ability to Slow a mob.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
